# Unified Ambulance Emergency System — Complete Agent Prompt

> This is the single source of truth for all three surfaces: Client App, Admin Dashboard, and Driver App.
> All developers, agents, and code generators must follow this specification exactly.

---

## System Overview

An Ambulance Emergency Booking System with three interconnected surfaces:

| Surface | Users | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Client App | Patients (public) | Request ambulances, choose company, track in real-time |
| Admin Dashboard | Company Admins / Super Admins | Manage ambulances, drivers, bookings, payments |
| Driver App | Registered drivers only | Receive requests, accept/deny, navigate to patient |

All three surfaces share a **single backend**, a **single database**, and communicate via **REST APIs + Socket.io real-time events**.

**Database:** SQLite3 (development) → PostgreSQL or MySQL (production)
**Maps:** React-Leaflet + OpenStreetMap (no API key required — used across all surfaces)
**Real-time:** Socket.io (primary), Firebase (optional fallback for location streams)

---

## 1. Authentication — One Smart Login System

### How It Works

There is **one single login page** shared by both admins and drivers.

- Admins log in with **Email + Password**
- Drivers log in with **Driver Name + Driver ID** (no email required)

After credentials are verified, the backend returns a `role` field:
- `super_admin` → redirect to Admin Dashboard
- `admin` → redirect to Admin Dashboard
- `driver` → redirect to Driver Dashboard

The frontend detects the role from the JWT payload and routes automatically. No manual navigation required.

---

### Admin Registration (Company Onboarding)

New companies register through a **"Register New Company"** form with:

- Full Name
- Company Name
- Email Address
- Password + Confirm Password
- Role Assignment: `Super Admin` | `Admin`

---

### Driver Registration (Admin-Side Only)

**Drivers cannot self-register.** Only an admin can create a driver account from inside the Admin Dashboard.

When an admin registers a driver, the system creates:

- Full Name
- Phone Number
- Auto-generated unique **Driver ID** (e.g. `DRV-00123`)
- Assigned Ambulance
- Driver Photo (optional)
- Login credentials: **Driver Name + Driver ID** (no email needed)

The admin shares the Driver Name and Driver ID with the driver. These are the only credentials the driver needs to log in.

---

### Shared Login Page Fields

**For Admins:**
- Email Address
- Password
- Remember Me checkbox → persistent session (30 days via httpOnly cookie or JWT with extended expiry)
- Forgot Password / Reset Password link
- Session timeout with auto-logout after inactivity

**For Drivers:**
- Driver Name
- Driver ID
- Remember Me checkbox

The login form detects which credential type is being entered and routes to the correct auth endpoint:
- Email format → `POST /auth/login/admin`
- Driver ID format → `POST /auth/login/driver`

---

### Auth Architecture

- JWT authentication (short-lived access tokens + long-lived refresh tokens)
- Role-based access control (RBAC): `super_admin`, `admin`, `driver`
- Refresh token rotation
- Secure httpOnly cookies for Remember Me
- Protected routes per role on the frontend — a driver cannot access admin routes and vice versa

