### Ambulance Management

- Register new ambulance: Ambulance Number, Driver assignment, GPS capability, Status
- Activate / Deactivate ambulances
- Monitor availability
- Status auto-updates to `busy` when a booking is accepted, back to `available` when trip is completed

---

### Driver Management (Admin-Side Only)

Admins register all drivers. No self-serve driver sign-up.

- Register new driver → system auto-generates Driver ID
- Share Driver Name + Driver ID with the driver for login
- Edit driver details
- View driver status: `available` | `on_trip` | `offline`
- Assign driver to ambulance unit

---

### Booking Requests Page

- Fetches from `GET /api/bookings?status=pending`
- Listens to `new_booking` Socket.io event → new requests appear instantly without page refresh
- Each request shows: Patient Name, Phone, Emergency Description, Patient location on Leaflet map
- Admin actions: **Assign Ambulance → Accept → Dispatch**
- On Accept: calls `PATCH /api/bookings/:id/accept`, emits `booking_accepted` to client + driver
- On Dispatch: calls `PATCH /api/bookings/:id/dispatch`, emits `ambulance_dispatched`
- Admin can see driver's response in real-time:
  - ✅ Driver Accepted → booking status updates to `accepted`
  - ❌ Driver Denied → admin is notified, can reassign to another driver
  - ⏳ No response within timeout → admin is notified, request flagged for reassignment

---

### Real-Time Tracking Map

- Leaflet + OpenStreetMap
- Live ambulance markers + patient markers per active booking
- Listens to `ambulance_location_update` and `patient_location_update` Socket.io events
- Admin can click any active booking marker to see full dispatch info

